history.content: I am currently enrolled in the 5 classes above. I feel really confused about which 4 classes I want to choose. This is my second to last semester at Berkeley. It looks like 184 and 267 are only offered in spring. I don't know if 168 is gonna be offered in fall and I think it is really useful because I am a backend/ database person. I heard 168's workload is relatively light compared to other classes. 267 is a class I want to take for my data science applied Math track. 184 looks really fun to me because I do arts and it looks like the only cs class where I can learn arts in 3d. 189 has a really good professor this semester. human happiness (philosophy) is one of the two breadths I have left and I am hoping it to bring me some fresh air...any advice is appreciated....thanks in advance!
history.subject: 168/184/189/267/human happiness (psych 162)
